==English==
===Etymology===
{{F.}} ''résolution''.  {{L.}} ''resolutio'' a loosening, solution.

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-uːʃən|-uːʃən]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
#the state of being [[resolute]]
#: ''His stalwart [[resolution]] is perhaps admirable, perhaps foolish.''
#a [[statement]] of [[intent]] (often [[New Year's resolution]])
#: ''My [[resolution]] is to cut back on the fast food this year.''
#(computing) the number of [[pixel]]s on the screen
#: ''Higher [[resolution]]s will cause a reduction in performance.''
#(hardware) the maximum number of [[pixel]]s that can be displayed on a [[monitor]]
#: ''This monitor's [[resolution]] is 600x800, on the low end of the spectrum.''
#A [[formal]] [[statement]] [[adopted]] by an [[assembly]]
#{{physics}} the [[separation]] of the [[constituent]] [[part]]s (of a spectrum etc)
#{{music}} Progression from [[dissonance]] to [[consonance]]; a [[chord]] to which such progression is made

